result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (2nd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (2nd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Holly M Nelson was found guilty of Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • Holly M Nelson was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Case called at 10:57 am [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Robert Mawdsley presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Holly M Nelson in court with Attorney Andrew Todd Rumpf. ADA Brookellen Teuber appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing recommendations by Counsel; Victim Rights Compliance Verified

On Count #1, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 30 months, concurrent, with conditions:
--To pay costs of $268
--To pay $250 DNA Surcharge
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand
--No operation of a motor vehicle without valid DL and Agent approval
--Absolute sobriety
--No presence in bars, taverns or liquor stores

On Count #2, the Court sentences the Defendant: 
--To serve 180 days in the Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges; to commence forthwith
--Defendant is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process
--To pay fine of $500 + costs = $1368 + $200 DNA Surcharge = $1568 + $56.74 blood testing costs = $1624.74; due in $50 increments per month beginning 12/1/14 and on the 1st day of the month thereafter until paid in full; non-payment will result in entry of civil judgment
--Revocation of drivers license for 18 months
--County alcohol/drug assessment ordered
--Victim impact panel attendance
--Ignition Interlock Device requirement/restrictions for: 18 months
--6 demerit points assessed

Days credit for time already served: 4 days (Ct. #2)
Felony Firearm/Voting Prohibitions Warnings Form Given
